<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-18T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-18T19:00:00-05:00" n="318" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d318">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">330/7–1850: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-18T20:00:00-04:00">July 18,
                                1950—8 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>88. Urtel 137 July 18. We urgently desire release messages 9:30 July 19
                        Washington time or not later than 10:30. Later release would conflict
                        important presidential statement. Inform Bajpai and cable urgently time of
                        release.</p>
                    <p>Re. para 4, <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> does not intend release
                        Nehru message rec’d here July 17.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>